The paper deals with the problem of approximating the $\ell_2$-distance from a given function to the closest $s$-sparse function, which is motivated by applications to fast sparse Fourier transforms over $\mathbb{F}_2^n$. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI), or Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
